File: Gautrain services have been hampered by load-shedding on Friday. PRETORIA - Gautrain services are back on track after they were hampered by load-shedding on Friday. The train service earlier said there were no trains between Midrand and Park Station as well as between Sandton and to OR Tambo International Airport. WATCH: Travelling in a Gautrain vs Metrorail It later said on Twitter that power has been restored and the train service is fully operational. Eskom on Thursday night implemented Stage 2 load-shedding, citing the loss of three more generation units and using its emergency reserves. 